FBIS4-43534 "drweu118_b_94002" FBIS-WEU-94-118 Daily Report 18 Jun 1994 BENELUX Belgium Government Rejects Sending Soldiers to Rwanda Government Rejects Sending Soldiers to Rwanda LD1806101394 Brussels Radio Vlaanderen International in English 0900 GMT 18 Jun 94 LD1806101394 Brussels Radio Vlaanderen International English BFN [Excerpt] [passage omitted] The Belgian Government has confirmed that our country will not send soldiers to Rwanda. According to Defense Minister Leo Delcroix, Belgium will, however, offer logistical support in the event of a military intervention. The Belgian Government has also earmarked 100 million francs for humanitarian help for the Rwandans. It will be organized by four Belgian nongovernmental organizations. [passage omitted]
